<item>
            <title>[FLINK-33939] Make husky in runtime-web no longer affect git global hooks</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-33939</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Since runtime-web relies on husky to ensure that front-end code changes are detected before `git commit`, husky modifies the global git hooks (core.hooksPath) so that core.hooksPath won&apos;t take effect if it&apos;s configured globally, I thought it would be a good idea to make the front-end code detection a optional command execution, which ensures that the globally configured hooks are executed correctly.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13562902">FLINK-33939</key>
            <summary>Make husky in runtime-web no longer affect git global hooks</summary>
